# Home Network Upgrade – Xfinity Gigabit Internet

## Project Overview
Upgraded a home network by replacing a Motorola MG8702 modem/router combo with a dedicated modem and router solution to improve performance, reliability, and future scalability.

## Hardware Used
- Modem: Hitron CODA56 DOCSIS 3.1 Cable Modem
- Router: TP-Link Archer BE550 Pro BE9700 Wi-Fi 7 Router
- ISP: Xfinity Gigabit Internet (1.1 Gbps Plan)
- Network Switch: Existing unmanaged Ethernet switch located in home office

## Objectives
- Improve wireless performance and network reliability
- Eliminate dependency on Motorola Moto Sync+ management platform
- Support current Gigabit internet speeds
- Future-proof home network with Wi-Fi 7 technology
- Maintain wired connectivity to office and gaming equipment

