## Implementation Steps
1. Verified existing coaxial cable connection and Xfinity compatibility.
2. Removed Motorola MG8702 modem/router combo.
3. Installed Hitron CODA56 modem and connected coaxial cable.
4. Connected modem to TP-Link Archer BE550 Pro using the 10 Gbps WAN port.
5. Connected existing Ethernet run to a LAN port on the router.
6. Activated the modem through Xfinity.
7. Configured Wi-Fi settings and security.
8. Verified internet connectivity and wired network functionality.
9. Reconnected smart home devices and Ring cameras to the new network.

## Troubleshooting Performed
- Verified coaxial cable connectivity.
- Confirmed proper WAN and LAN port assignments.
- Diagnosed Xfinity modem activation issues.
- Validated Ethernet connectivity to the office switch.
- Identified offline smart home devices after Wi-Fi migration.
- Restored connectivity by updating wireless settings and reconnecting devices.

